      "id": "PopularPost333044",
      "post_content": "Reanimation engine, thy name is [Scion of the Ur-Dragon](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Scion of the Ur-Dragon).   \n  \nIn a dedicated Commander deck, it wouldn't be unreasonable to toss a lot of your Dragons into the graveyard just to bring them all back out with such toys as [Debtors' Knell](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Debtors' Knell), [Immortal Servitude](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Immortal Servitude), and [Rise of the Dark Realms](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rise of the Dark Realms). Complement those with simpler spells like [Beacon of Unrest](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Beacon of Unrest), [Dread Return](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dread Return), and [Vigor Mortis](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vigor Mortis). Of course, there's always the tribal option in cards like [Bladewing the Risen](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bladewing the Risen) and [Teneb, the Harvester](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Teneb, the Harvester) as well.  \n  \nLong story short, pack some reanimator if you make a deck with [Scion of the Ur-Dragon](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Scion of the Ur-Dragon). You won't regret it.",
      "posted_by": "TheWallinator74",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost333044\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">Reanimation engine, thy name is <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Scion of the Ur-Dragon\">Scion of the Ur-Dragon</a>. <br/><br/>In a dedicated Commander deck, it wouldn't be unreasonable to toss a lot of your Dragons into the graveyard just to bring them all back out with such toys as <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Debtors' Knell\">Debtors' Knell</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Immortal Servitude\">Immortal Servitude</a>, and <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rise of the Dark Realms\">Rise of the Dark Realms</a>. Complement those with simpler spells like <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Beacon of Unrest\">Beacon of Unrest</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dread Return\">Dread Return</a>, and <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vigor Mortis\">Vigor Mortis</a>. Of course, there's always the tribal option in cards like <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bladewing the Risen\">Bladewing the Risen</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Teneb, the Harvester\">Teneb, the Harvester</a> as well.<br/><br/>Long story short, pack some reanimator if you make a deck with <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Scion of the Ur-Dragon\">Scion of the Ur-Dragon</a>. You won't regret it.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00